name: Václav Jan Tomášek
comments: Composer and music teacher, known as the Musical Pope of Prague. In 1815 he started to write 41 songs that were set to poems of Johann Wolfgang von Goethe . In 1818 all the songs were published privately in 6 seperate songbooks titled "Gedichte von Goethe für den Gesang mit Begleitung des Piano-Forte" (op. 53-61). He sent some of them to the poet on spec. The two men corresponded and subsequently met at a Czech spa, where Tomášek touched the aged poet with songs including "Heidenröslein". Goethe even liked them more than the Schubert settings of his poems.
